So, assuming we can&#39;t use either `SwingWorker` or Swing `Timer`, as they create a second thread to support their operations, the only choice you&#39;re left with is to use `SwingUtilities#invokeLater` to repeatedly call a method, which performs a small subset of the work and updates the UI before calling itself again (using `SwingUtilities#invokeLater`)

[![Look ma, no threads][1]][1]

	import java.awt.EventQueue;
